          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The He-6 beam was produced by the Li-7(p,2p)He-6",
                "reaction in a LiF powder target with a graphite",
                "container."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two different types of target were used in the present",
                "experiment.",
                "Targets of Type I were a layer of enriched more than",
                " 97% Pb-206 metal of 0.50+-0.05 mg/cm**2 thickness",
                "evaporated on a 40 mug/cm**2 thin Carbon foil.",
                "According to TRIM calculation the thickness of the",
                "Carbon backing was sufficient to stop the fusion",
                "produced Po-210 evaporation residues.",
                "Targets of Type II were made by depositing a disk-",
                "shaped layer 15 mm diameter of 206PbS compound on",
                " 1.5 mum thick Ti foils. The material used was of",
                "enrichment more than 95%, effective 206Pb thickness of",
                "around 1 mg/cm**2. The Ti foils served as beam energy",
                "degraders."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Charged particles emitted by the scattering",
                "target were detected by the large area Si multi-",
                "detector system LEDA. One LEDA array is an annular",
                "detector consisting of 8 sectors, each having 16 strips",
                "of 10 mm width. Forward and backward scattering angles",
                "were covered by 2 LAMP(The removal of two sectors from",
                "LEDA assembly enables the remaining sectors to be",
                "arranged as a six-sided cone-colloquially know as",
                "the LAMP configuration) sets of 5 LEDA sectors each."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " All irradiated samples were subjected to a",
                "chemical processing, known amounts of 209Pb tracer were",
                "added, Po material extracted and induced alpha-",
                "radioactivity measured at  Huelva University. The total",
                "stack thickness and a beam energy spread were measured",
                "in a special experimental run of a low beam intensity."
              ]
            }
          ],
